
** Keys

  - C-c C-l       - prints the history
  - C-c <SPC>/C-j - accumulate (inserts a newline)
  - C-c C-c       - interrupt
  - C-c C-z
  - C-c C-o       - comint-flush-output (last output)
  - C-c C-u       - comint-kill-input (alternative C-a C-k)
  - C-c C-w       - backward-kill-word
  - C-c C-s       - write last output to a file
  - C-c C-r       - scroll to beginning of last output
  - C-c C-e       - scroll to the end

** To scroll down a shell buffer use

  - comint-scroll-show-maximum-output
  - comint-scroll-to-bottom-on-output

** Change Coding System

  - *C-x RET p* set-buffer-process-coding-system

** Accumulate

<example>
  $ ls tmp
    ls build
</exampel>
